725022f-a.title: Queens: 14th Avenue - 118th Street
725022f-a.text:
14th Avenue, north side, between 118th and 119th Streets, showing the First Reformed Church of College Point and the
chapel (right).
P. L. Sperr  March 12, 1932

725021f-a.title: Queens: 14th Avenue - 118th Street
725021f-a.text:
14th Avenue, north side, at 118th Street, showing an old mansion. It was owned by the Ruhl family in 1873 and 1891. 14th Avenue, here, was then named First Avenue.
P.L.Sperr  March 12, 1932
